# LoopOS runtime temp status files (path-encoded stray artifacts).
*.loopos-tmp-status.txt

# Windows reserved device name strays (NUL/CON/PRN/AUX/COM*/LPT*) that some
# shells redirecting to "nul" can materialize as 0-byte entries. These cannot
# be deleted by normal rm/del because Windows resolves them to device handles,
# so we ignore them to keep the working tree clean and prevent `mypy .` from
# crashing on path resolution.
nul
CON
PRN
AUX
COM1
COM2
COM3
COM4
LPT1
LPT2
LPT3
LPT4
